article.headline: Ball State 88, Ohio 84 (OT)
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Jaivon Harris scored 26 points and made his seventh 3-pointer with 43 seconds remaining in overtime, giving Ohio the lead for good in its 88-84 win over Ball State on Saturday. Harris' basket put the Bobcats (8-13, 5-6 Mid-American Conference) ahead 85-82. The Cardinals (9-10, 6-5) got within one when Peyton Stovall made two free throws with 29 seconds remaining. Terren Harbut made one of two free throws to give Ohio an 86-84 lead with 25 seconds left, and Ball State missed two chances to tie. Dennis Trammell missed a jumper with 15 seconds remaining. Stovall, whose layup at the end of regulation sent the game to overtime, missed a layup with 11 seconds remaining. Stovall also committed a turnover with three seconds left after Jeff Halbert hit two free throws to give the Bobcats an 88-84 lead. Matt McCollom led the Cardinals with 23 points. Trammell scored 15, Robert Owens and Cameron Echols added 12 apiece and Stovall had 10. Trammell's layup with 52 seconds left in regulation pulled Ball State to 75-73, and the Cardinals tied it on Stovall's layup with six seconds to play. Thomas Stephens missed a jumper for Ohio at the buzzer. Harris made 7-of-15 from 3-point range and the Bobcats connected on 13-of-30 beyond the arc. Ball State missed 19 of its 24 3-point shots. Ohio also had a large edge at the foul line, making 31-of-38 free throws to 17-of-24 for the Cardinals. Harbut scored 15 points, Stephens added 13, Sonny Troutman had 11 and Halbert 10 for the Bobcats. Delvar Barrett had 11 points and 10 rebounds.
